rComments: Tests are tough but he helps a lot during office hours. Do the homework and you're good.

The lectures are pretty good, He's very clear on the expectations. Lack of experience showed a bit when creating the exams but he curved up in a reasonable way to compensate for it. Overall a pretty good experience.

Nice guy and willing to go a long way for his students. Explanations are often clear, and when they are not he clarifies them upon request. Make sure to know your stuff from last lecture though because he expects you to keep up.

rComments: His lectures are ok. The material was dry (calculus) and since it was the summer, I wasn't really in the mood to go to an early class for math.
